Vice President Mike Pence spoke at SCHOTT North America in Pennsylvania to celebrate the company's 50th anniversary. He praised the company for its contributions to national defense, including providing equipment to the armed forces. Pence also highlighted the Trump administration's accomplishments, such as tax cuts, deregulation, and job creation. He urged Congress to pass the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA), stating that it would benefit Pennsylvania and the entire country. Pence called on the people of Pennsylvania to contact their elected officials and express their support for the USMCA. He ended his speech by expressing his faith in the American people and their ability to unite and achieve greatness.